              <a:t>The switch is mandatory. load_stores() in rag/stores.py throws NotImplementedError for any other backend — that's intentional. The psycopg2 ThreadedConnectionPool initializes at startup via init_pool(), and apply_schema() runs the schema SQL so it's safe to call repeatedly. pgvector provides the vector column type and HNSW indexing for approximate nearest neighbor search, with cosine distance via the &lt;=&gt; operator. Embedding dimension is configurable and we provide utilities to dynamically ALTER the column dimension if you swap embedding models — drops the HNSW index, alters the column, lets you rebuild. Full-text search uses PostgreSQL's built-in tsvector for BM25-style keyword matching alongside vector search.</a:t>
